<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <title>Unseen Neighbors — Homelessness in Our Community</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css" />
</head>
<body>

  <!-- ===== HEADER ===== -->
  <header>
    <div class="header-inner">
      <h1>Unseen Neighbors</h1>
      <p class="tagline">Everyone knows. Almost no one talks. But the people living it can't afford to look away.</p>
    </div>
  </header>

  <!-- ===== NAVIGATION ===== -->
  <nav aria-label="Main navigation">
    <a href="#about">About the Issue</a>
    <a href="#matters">Why It Matters</a>
    <a href="#action">Take Action</a>
    <a href="#resources">Resources</a>
  </nav>

  <!-- ===== SECTION 1: About the Issue ===== -->
  <section id="about" class="section section-light">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>About the Issue</h2>

      <p>
        Homelessness is one of the most visible — and most ignored — crises in America.
        We walk past it every day on the way to class, on the train, in the park.
        We've learned to look the other direction. But for millions of people,
        there is no other direction to look.
      </p>

      <p>
        In the U.S., <strong>771,000</strong> people experience homelessness on any given night,
        according to the U.S. Department of Housing and Urban Development. These aren't strangers
        from somewhere else — they're people from our own neighborhoods, schools, and families
        who hit a moment they couldn't recover from alone.
      </p>

      <!-- Student's personal story — kept exactly as written -->
      <blockquote class="personal-story">
        I've been aware of homelessness from a young age. I'd see people out on the streets,
        having to hold up signs for hours on end just in the hopes that someone might be kind
        enough to let them live another day. I believe that no one should have to worry about
        where they're going to sleep tomorrow, so I decided to see what I could do to raise awareness.
      </blockquote>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ===== SECTION 2: Why It Matters ===== -->
  <section id="matters" class="section section-dark">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Why It Matters</h2>

      <!-- Stat cards -->
      <div class="card-grid">
        <div class="card">
          <span class="card-number">700,000+</span>
          <span class="card-label">people experience homelessness in the U.S. each year</span>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <span class="card-number">60%</span>
          <span class="card-label">of people experiencing homelessness are employed but still can't afford housing</span>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <span class="card-number">42 years</span>
          <span class="card-label">average life expectancy of a person experiencing chronic homelessness</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p>
        Homelessness isn't a personal failure — it's a systems failure. Job loss, medical debt,
        domestic violence, mental health crises, and housing costs that have outpaced wages
        are all paths that can lead someone to the street. It can happen faster than most people think.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ===== SECTION 3: Take Action ===== -->
  <section id="action" class="section section-light">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Take Action</h2>

      <p class="section-intro">
        You don't need a lot of money or connections to make a difference.
        Here are three real things you can do this week.
      </p>

      <div class="action-list">

        <!-- Action 01 -->
        <div class="action-item">
          <span class="action-number" aria-hidden="true">01</span>
          <div class="action-body">
            <h3>Learn the local landscape</h3>
            <p>
              Spend 20 minutes researching what organizations in your city serve people experiencing
              homelessness. Most cities have a 211 hotline or website that maps services. Knowing
              what exists is the first step toward connecting others to help — or volunteering yourself.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Action 02 -->
        <div class="action-item">
          <span class="action-number" aria-hidden="true">02</span>
          <div class="action-body">
            <h3>Talk about it out loud</h3>
            <p>
              Bring it up in class, at the dinner table, or in a group chat. Silence is part of
              what keeps this issue invisible. You don't need all the answers. Asking "why does
              this keep happening in our neighborhood?" out loud is enough to start a real conversation.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Action 03 -->
        <div class="action-item">
          <span class="action-number" aria-hidden="true">03</span>
          <div class="action-body">
            <h3>Donate what you can</h3>
            <p>
              Local shelters frequently need volunteers and basic supplies: socks, hygiene products,
              non-perishable food. Check if your school or campus has a drive, or organize one.
              Even a single donation run matters more than doing nothing while waiting to do something big.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div><!-- /.action-list -->

      <p class="safety-note">Always stay safe and follow school/family rules when getting involved in community action.</p>

      <!-- Call-to-action button -->
      <a href="#resources" class="cta-button">Find a Local Organization</a>

    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ===== SECTION 4: Resources ===== -->
  <section id="resources" class="section section-dark">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Resources</h2>
      <p>Start here to learn more, get involved, or find help:</p>

      <ul class="resource-list">

        <li>
          <strong>National Alliance to End Homelessness</strong> —
          <a href="https://endhomelessness.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener">endhomelessness.org</a>
          <br /><span class="resource-desc">Research, policy, and a map of local organizations.</span>
        </li>

        <li>
          <strong>211 Helpline</strong> —
          <a href="https://www.211.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener">211.org</a> or dial 2-1-1
          <br /><span class="resource-desc">Connects people to local social services including shelter and food.</span>
        </li>

        <li>
          <strong>HUD Exchange</strong> —
          <a href="https://www.hudexchange.info" target="_blank" rel="noopener">hudexchange.info</a>
          <br /><span class="resource-desc">Federal data, reports, and funding information on homelessness.</span>
        </li>

      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ===== FOOTER ===== -->
  <footer>
    <div class="container">
      <p class="footer-small">
        This site is for educational purposes. If you or someone you know needs immediate shelter,
        call <strong>211</strong> or visit <a href="https://www.211.org">211.org</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </footer>

</body>
</html>
